The paper discusses machine learning algorithms and statistical guarantees, which are typically studied in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of differential privacy and Bayesian methods suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), respectively. The concentration result and learning-theoretic proof may also relate to data structures (cs.DS) and statistics (cs.ST).
